UID:120312-1776542400-1776547800@naturalsciences.org
SUMMARY:Ghost Firefly Survey
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that we have ghost fireflies in the Piedmont?  Join us for this program for ages 14+ to survey Prairie Ridge to see if our sites hosts these amazing insects!  We’ll start with a brief introduction to the ghost fireflies and the protocols for data collection if we spot them\, then we’ll spend 30-45 minutes in the woods looking for trails of blue firefly light. Dress for the weather\, wear closed toed shoes\, bring a flashlight\, water\, and an optional chair\, and you’ll be ready to look for small fireflies with us! \nRegistration is required to attend this program. \nRegister
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/ghost-firefly-survey/
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge\, 1671 Gold Star Drive\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Citizen Science,Outdoor Experiences,Teens
ORGANIZER;CN="Chris%20Goforth":MAILTO:chris.goforth@naturalsciences.org
GEO:35.812182885871;-78.713963528554
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Prairie Ridge 1671 Gold Star Drive Raleigh NC 27607 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=1671 Gold Star Drive:geo:-78.713963528554,35.812182885871
END:VEVENT
