SUMMARY:How to Bioblitz
DESCRIPTION:Bioblitzes are events where everyone is invited to help document the species living in an area. In this virtual program\, we’ll walk you through what a bioblitz is and how it works\, then provide some training so you can earn the ecoEXPLORE bioblitz badge! \nThis virtual program is especially for kids in grades K-8\, but everyone is welcome.  You do not need to join ecoEXPLORE before the program\, but should you choose to create an account for your child so they can get started documenting wildlife for scientists and earning prizes\, visit ecoexplore.net. \nRegister here
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/how-to-bioblitz/
LOCATION:Virtual\, NC\, United States
CATEGORIES:Children,Citizen Science,K-12 Students,Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="ecoEXPLORE%20Team":MAILTO:ecoexplore@naturalsciences.org
END:VEVENT
